    {
      "id": "sticky-no-sops",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "Think: “I have been doing it myself / I know how to do it:\n\nNo defined SOPs, structured data, etc\n\nYour job as the AI Engineer is to figure out what data is needed and how to collect it based on the clients goals.\n- Start collecting call transcripts\n- Start storing out support tickets",
      "color": "yellow",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 96,
        "y": 160,
        "width": 432,
        "height": 512
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-rarely-labeled",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "Most companies I work with have data, but rarely have it labeled already\n- The only case I have see where there were “labels” was closed customer support tickets\n- 95%+ of the time the data will not be labeled",
      "color": "yellow",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 2064,
        "y": 160,
        "width": 432,
        "height": 432
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-labels-shortcut",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "If there are already labels, we can go directly to working on the classification model\n\nIf the data is not labeled, then we need to have the client label a dataset we create so that we have something to test on",
      "color": "yellow",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 2576,
        "y": 1008,
        "width": 432,
        "height": 416
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-client-must-label",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "The client or some subject matter expert MUST label the data.\n\nIf we want the eval to be aligned with the clients goals / preferences, they MUST impart the preferences themselves",
